HEADWORD: Dietetics
<hw>Di`e*tet"ics</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>That part of the
medical or hygienic art which relates to diet or food; rules for
diet.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To suppose that the whole of <qex>dietetics</qex> lies in
determining whether or not bread is more nutritive than potatoes.</q>
<rj><qau>H. Spencer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dietetist</ent>⟦br⟧
